S|# 🔬 Research Report: Context Intelligence Engine (CIE)|
S|Plugin for YVON OS — v1 Architecture & Implementation Plan|> **Request:** Transform TOON compression into a plugin (like graphify/codegraph) that connects with knw graphs, project mem, agt self-improvement files, and Hermes mem to produce better agt outputs. // **Date:** 2026-06-11   // **Author:** Marcus (CEO) — research synthesis   // **Status:** Plan — awaiting Stark ap to build // ---
S|1. WHAT EXISTS NOW (Landscape)|### 1.1 knw Graphs // \| System \| What It Maps \| Format \| Queryable \| // \|--------\|-------------\|--------\|:---------:\| // \| **graphify** \| AST-level code structure → 1,058 nodes, 1,807 edges, 119 communities \| GRAPH_REPORT.md (31KB) \| ✅ `python3 -m graphify query "<q>"` \| // \| **codegraph** \| Import/dependency graph → 355 files, 575 edges \| CODEGRAPH_REPORT.md \| ✅ `node scripts/codegraph-build.mjs` \| // **graphify communities show functional clusters:** // - Community 6 → agt 
S|2. THE GAP — Why Output Quality Suffers|### Problem A: Agents are blind to the codebase // When Dev debugs a build error, the LLM has: // - ✅ The error message // - ❌ No knw of which files import the failing module // - ❌ No awareness that changing `lib/types.ts` affects 72 other files // - ❌ No visibility into Community 6 (agt mem functions) when debugging a mem issue // **Result:** The LLM proposes fixes without understanding blast radius. Broke `types.ts` → 72 files fail → 30-minute recovery. // ### Problem B: Agents forget their o
S|3. THE SOLUTION — Context Intelligence Engine (CIE)|### 3.1 Architecture // ``` // ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ // │                    API ROUTE LAYER                           │ // │  /api/claude  │  /api/agt-cron/*  │  /api/team-chat      │ // └───────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘ //                 │  ClaudeRequestBody {agentId, task, vtr, ...} //                 ▼ // ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ // │              CIE PLUGIN (lib/cie/)             
S|4. IMPLEMENTATION PLAN|### Phase 1: Foundation (lib/cie/ core + injection) — ~3 hours // **Files to create:** // ``` // lib/cie/ // ├── index.ts            # Main entry: buildCieContext(params) → {systemExtension, dataBlock} // ├── classifier.ts       # classifyTask(agentId, message, vtr) → TaskType // ├── retriever.ts        # retrieveContext(taskType, agentId, vtr) → ContextSources // ├── builder.ts          # buildSystemExtension(sources) + buildDataBlock(sources) → strings // ├── weights.ts          # getWeights(a
S|5. ADD-ON FEATURES (Future)|### 5.1 CIE Skill Generator // When CIE detects a pattern (e.g., "codegraph deps reduced errors 40% for dev agt"), it auto-creates a Hermes skill: // ``` // Skill: cie-dev-backend-pattern // When: backend_bug task + dev agt // Include: codegraph hub files + Never Again rules + architecture locks // Exclude: vtr DESIGN.md, mkt ctx // ``` // Skills accumulate and auto-load on future matching tasks. // ### 5.2 Cross-agt ctx Sharing // When Henry (CEO) delegates to Dev (CTO), CIE auto-injects: // - 
S|6. BENCHMARKS (Projected)|### Token Impact // \| Scenario \| Without CIE \| With CIE \| Savings \| // \|----------\|:-----------:\|:--------:\|:-------:\| // \| Henry filters 50 decisions \| 6,288 tokens \| 1,200 tokens \| **81%** \| // \| Dev debugs build error \| 4,200 tokens \| 1,800 tokens \| **57%** \| // \| Mia builds component \| 3,500 tokens \| 2,100 tokens \| **40%** \| // \| War Room synthesis \| 12,000 tokens \| 5,500 tokens \| **54%** \| // \| Quinn pulse check \| 2,800 tokens \| 1,400 tokens \| **50%** \| //
S|7. RISKS & MITIGATIONS|\| Risk \| Likelihood \| Impact \| Mitigation \| // \|------\|:---------:\|:------:\|-----------\| // \| ctx explosion (too much ctx degrades quality) \| Medium \| High \| Hard caps: 2,500 chars total, 600 per source. Auto-prune on quality drop. \| // \| graphify GRAPH_REPORT.md stale (>30 days old) \| Medium \| Medium \| CIE checks file mtime. Warns if >14 days. Skips if >30 days. \| // \| Never Again rules conflict (marcus says X, dev says Y) \| Low \| Medium \| Priority: architecture locks > 
S|8. DECISION REQUIRED|**Should we build this?** // **Arguments for:** // - Existing systems (graphify, codegraph, agt mem, TOON) are already built — CIE is the integration layer that makes them work together // - Projected 40-81% token savings per call // - Projected 20% accuracy improvement for Dev agt // - Self-improving — gets better over time without manual tuning // - Zero breaking changes — opt-in per route, backward compatible // - Makes all 13 agents smarter simultaneously // **Arguments against:** // - Adds 
S|9. BUILD ORDER|``` // Phase 1: lib/cie/ core (types, classifier, builder, index)     → make it inject // Phase 2: knw retrievers (graphify, codegraph, mem)     → make it smart // Phase 3: Self-improvement (weights, outcomes, dashboard)        → make it learn // Phase 4: Integration (wire into all agt routes)               → make it live // ``` // **Each phase is independently deployable.** Phase 1 alone provides immediate value (smart ctx injection with caps). Phases 2-4 add intelligence and learning. // --- /